General Assembly House Joint
Resolution No. 59
February Session, 2026 LCO No. 2222
Referred to Committee on EXECUTIVE AND LEGISLATIVE
NOMINATIONS
Introduced by:
REP. CONCEPCION, 4th Dist.
SEN. DUFF, 25th Dist.
RESOLUTION CONFIRMING THE NOMINATION OF JANICE
BEECHER OF NEW BRITAIN TO BE A UTILITY COMMISSIONER OF
THE PUBLIC UTILITIES REGULATORY AUTHORITY.
Resolved by this Assembly:
1 That the nomination by His Excellency, the Governor, of Janice
2 Beecher of New Britain to be appointed a utility commissioner of the
3 Public Utilities Regulatory Authority, in succession to Katherine Scharf
4 Dykes, to serve a term ending June 30, 2030, or until a successor is
5 appointed and has qualified, whichever is longer, is hereby approved
6 and confirmed.
LCO No. 2222 1 of 1

